00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:18,180
What nonsense!

575
00:29:18,540 --> 00:29:20,260
Did you think that you
can manipulate the Empress Dowager

576
00:29:20,660 --> 00:29:22,660
like what you did with His Majesty?

577
00:29:22,660 --> 00:29:23,380
Empress Dowager,

578
00:29:23,980 --> 00:29:25,660
this person is ominous,

579
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:27,820
don't believe a word he said.

580
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:31,140
His Majesty is the son of the heaven.

581
00:29:31,820 --> 00:29:33,420
How is it possible
that he's surrounded by a bad aura?

582
00:29:33,980 --> 00:29:35,220
You're just making things up.

583
00:29:35,580 --> 00:29:36,820
Do you have proof?

584
00:29:39,860 --> 00:29:42,580
I implore that the Empress Dowager
bring His Majesty here

585
00:29:42,580 --> 00:29:43,780
and I'll demonstrate it.

586
00:29:44,660 --> 00:29:45,260
Empress Dowager,

587
00:29:45,540 --> 00:29:46,860
he's just using you

588
00:29:46,860 --> 00:29:48,500
to summon His Majesty here
to save himself.

589
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,580
You must not fall into his trap.

590
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:52,380
Empress Dowager,

591
00:29:52,980 --> 00:29:54,940
this person pretended
to be the Emissary,

592
00:29:55,220 --> 00:29:56,500
manipulated the people

593
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:58,500
and prevented His Majesty
from consummating.

594
00:29:58,860 --> 00:30:00,500
It should be a death penalty.

595
00:30:02,180 --> 00:30:02,860
Empress Dowager,

596
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:06,500
we should send him to prison

597
00:30:06,620 --> 00:30:08,300
and I'll interrogate him myself.

598
00:30:08,660 --> 00:30:10,260
Once the truth is out,

599
00:30:10,260 --> 00:30:11,500
he'll be beheaded immediately.

600
00:30:13,900 --> 00:30:17,020
We'll just follow
Chancellor Cui's advice.

601
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:18,620
The Empress Dowager is wise.

602
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:41,180
Say it,

603
00:30:43,980 --> 00:30:45,260
who instructed you

604
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:46,820
to suddenly appear

605
00:30:46,820 --> 00:30:48,780
in the rain praying ritual?

606
00:30:49,620 --> 00:30:51,580
And who instructed you

607
00:30:52,460 --> 00:30:54,340
to prevent His Majesty
from consummating?

608
00:30:54,980 --> 00:30:56,340
I've said it many times.

609
00:30:57,540 --> 00:30:58,140
No one.

610
00:30:58,500 --> 00:30:59,820
There's really no one.

611
00:30:59,820 --> 00:31:02,180
You're really stubborn.

612
00:31:13,620 --> 00:31:14,580
Wake him up!

613
00:31:21,100 --> 00:31:22,420
You've been in the palace for so long,

614
00:31:23,220 --> 00:31:24,820
do you know what is the lingering death?

615
00:31:26,220 --> 00:31:27,620
I'll tell you now.

616
00:31:28,060 --> 00:31:29,540
It means I'll use this knife

617
00:31:29,540 --> 00:31:30,900
to cut off

618
00:31:30,900 --> 00:31:32,740
your body bit by bit

619
00:31:33,420 --> 00:31:36,020
till you wish you were dead.

620
00:31:38,100 --> 00:31:39,220
I want to see His Majesty.

621
00:31:39,220 --> 00:31:40,340
Do you think you can see His Majesty

622
00:31:40,340 --> 00:31:41,380
whenever you want to?

623
00:31:41,380 --> 00:31:41,900
Say it!

624
00:31:41,900 --> 00:31:43,140
Who is the instigator?

625
00:31:43,140 --> 00:31:44,060
There's really no one!

626
00:31:44,060 --> 00:31:45,100
There isn't!

627
00:31:46,220 --> 00:31:47,260
Alright,

628
00:31:48,140 --> 00:31:50,420
then let's start with your face.

629
00:31:56,860 --> 00:31:57,940
Stop it!

630
00:32:21,620 --> 00:32:24,860
♪When a gust of wind brushes past♪

631
00:32:24,860 --> 00:32:28,420
♪The sand and the wind
burn with passion♪

632
00:32:28,420 --> 00:32:31,500
♪Unafraid to forego a chance
to quench our thirst♪

633
00:32:31,500 --> 00:32:35,300
♪Like camels walking with eyes closed♪

634
00:32:35,300 --> 00:32:38,420
♪When the rain falls
into a rare silence♪

635
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:42,140
♪Thinking of hardships
you and I don't know♪

636
00:32:42,140 --> 00:32:45,140
♪No need to hum the wind's song♪

637
00:32:45,140 --> 00:32:49,220
♪Uncaring of the darkening skies♪

638
00:32:49,220 --> 00:32:50,900
♪I understood all that for you♪

639
00:32:50,900 --> 00:32:52,660
♪But you have disappeared♪

640
00:32:52,660 --> 00:32:54,340
♪I am lost in the dark♪

641
00:32:54,340 --> 00:32:56,060
♪How should I stop?♪

642
00:32:56,060 --> 00:32:57,740
♪Loving you feels like another lifetime♪

643
00:32:57,740 --> 00:33:01,420
♪But yearning flows into a poem♪

644
00:33:01,420 --> 00:33:04,380
♪For us to meet again♪

645
00:33:04,380 --> 00:33:07,740
♪Requires the promise of millenia♪

646
00:33:07,740 --> 00:33:09,980
♪Watching the rain hail down♪

647
00:33:09,980 --> 00:33:15,060
♪It's like you're still beside me♪

648
00:33:15,060 --> 00:33:18,020
♪When I want to cross over♪

649
00:33:18,020 --> 00:33:22,100
♪To touch you♪

650
00:33:22,100 --> 00:33:24,540
♪But I can't see your fading face♪

651
00:33:24,540 --> 00:33:28,820
♪On the opposite shore♪

652
00:33:28,820 --> 00:33:31,820
♪How do I voice this?♪

653
00:33:31,820 --> 00:33:35,220
♪My heart beats uneasily♪

654
00:33:35,220 --> 00:33:38,140
♪How I long to hold tight♪

655
00:33:38,140 --> 00:33:42,500
♪To the loneliness in your hands♪

656
00:33:42,500 --> 00:33:45,500
♪Yet you warn me♪

657
00:33:45,500 --> 00:33:49,540
♪Any closer and I'll set in stone♪

658
00:33:49,540 --> 00:33:51,140
♪The sunset deep in your heart♪

659
00:33:51,140 --> 00:33:59,020
♪Of the day you most loved me♪
